<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Human Resources (HR) leverages leadership in the marketplace, and enables the company to drive revenue by attracting, developing and retaining a world&ndash;class workforce. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
A strategic partner with our business and corporate groups, HR provides the expertise essential for maximising employees' professional achievement and personal success. Working together, specialist and generalist areas provide a comprehensive service to our clients. They drive the people management aspects of the overall business strategy by delivering superior HR policy development, strategic HR advice, reward and retention programmes, management of employee relations, resourcing, diversity, learning and development, and compensation and benefits. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
As an Analyst within HR, you&#39;ll: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Be part of a leading team of professionals, and partner an outstanding internal client base, comprising leaders in their products and markets</li>
	<li>Rotate around different areas of HR</li>
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities</li>
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>
	<li>Collaborate on exciting projects that contribute to business success and next&ndash;generation advances</li>
	<li>Work with your team to create an environment for competitive advantage, and promote an internal and external reputation for excellence </li>
	<li>Pursue meritocracy and empower every individual to maximise their potential </li>
	<li>Connect as one HR team, share ownership and accountability for one HR agenda, and leverage HR expertise through true partnership </li>
	<li>Understand the part that HR plays in achieving business results</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
You must be able to combine academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking, and written and oral communications skills. In addition, you must have obtained, or are realistically expecting to obtain, a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Whether new graduates, or seasoned professionals, expanding the skills of the associates is paramount to achieving success. That&#39;s why Bank of America Merrill Lynch places a great deal of emphasis on on&ndash;going training for all staff. Training modules are available at all levels from product specific courses, to generic soft skills development. Specialised industry training will be principally on&ndash;the&ndash;job.  
</p>

